SIMPLE: liveryman
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Liveryman
<hw>Liv"er*y*man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Liverymen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
wears a livery, as a servant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A freeman of the city, in London, who, having paid
certain fees, is entitled to wear the distinguishing dress or
<xex>livery</xex> of the company, guild, or district to which he
belongs, and also to enjoy certain other privileges, as the right of
voting in an election for the lord mayor, sheriffs, chamberlain,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One who keeps a livery stable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Livery stable</ent>⟦br⟧
